description: Take part in an exciting opportunity to grow your programming skills. Throughout the course of the day, you will be sorted into groups and get the chance to build a project with like-minded youth. No programming experience necessary and intended for students!
Present your science or STEM related projects to experts in the area and your peers! Over $1000 in prizes available!
A week-long opportunity to learn the basics of progrmaming from upper year computer science students at the University of Waterloo! Open to students in middle school through high school.

eventname: University of Waterloo Outreach Co-op Opportunity
description: While earning credits from your school's co-op program, you'll be able to work under an engineering professor at the Univeristy of Waterloo. Avaliable to grade 11 and grade 12 students.

Are you fascinated by robots? Would you love the opportunity to build one alongside other students? Consider joining the Waterloo FIRST robotics team. You'll be able to develop new skills and make some new friends along the way. We also compete in a tournament near the end of the year!
The University of Waterloo is offering a math contest for senior high school students. Prizes available for the top performing students.
A four-week STEAM based summer enrichment program. Students spend a month living in a residence at the University of Waterloo.
Attention all computer science lovers! A new club is starting up for all those interested in programming. No experience necessary!
The Waterloo STEM council is an organization that aims to provide unique STEM related events for our students. We would love new members with a fresh perspective to join!
Are you a woman in engineering? Would you like to connect with other women in your field? Consider joining the Waterloo Women in Engineering chapter!
Come out to the Kitchener Math Symposium and check out presentation from various math professors! Everyone is welcome to come and learn!
Come check out the awesome projects our local design teams have been working! There will also be recruiting events and information on how you can get involved with a design team!
Join the Kitchener engineering camp to learn more about the construction in Kitchener
